“妈妈出院，我爸去世的消息瞒不住了”。
"I can't keep the news of my father's death from the hospital.
澎湃新闻。
The news is roaring.
澎湃新闻                      。
The news is roaring.
澎湃新闻。
The news is roaring.
有内涵的时政新媒体。
Connotation of the new political media.
武汉市青山区市民 夏女士澎湃新闻记者 薛莎莎 整理夏女士家住武汉市青山区，家中七口人：公婆、父母、丈夫、她和三岁大的孩子。
Ms. Xue Sha Sha, a journalist from Qingshan District, Wuhan City, lives in the Qingshan area of Wuhan City. There are seven members of her family: her mother-in-law, her parents, her husband, her three-year-old child.
此前，澎湃新闻曾报道了她一家七口疑似感染新冠肺炎的故事。
Earlier, Peng Pai News had reported the story of seven members of her family suspected of contracting New Crown Pneumonia.
她公婆、丈夫先后查出肺部感染或病变，住进了武汉市第九医院的隔离病房。
Her mother-in-law, her husband has detected lung infection or pathological changes, live in Wuhan City Ninth Hospital isolation ward.
她父母肺部也感染，此前在武汉市中心医院治疗。
Her parents, whose lungs were also infected, had been treated at Wuhan Central Hospital.
随后，公婆、丈夫和母亲所做的新冠病毒核酸检测，均呈阳性。
Subsequently, the mother-in-law, husband and mother-in-law tested positive for the new crown virus nucleic acid.
夏女士10日做的CT检查报告显示“复查有好转趋势”。
Ms. Xia did the CT examination report on the 10th showed that "review has an improvement trend."
本文图片均由夏女士供图2月4日上午，年逾六旬的父亲在住院治疗期间“突发重症”抢救无效离世，她和家人未能见到父亲最后一面。
Photo by Ms. Xia Feb 4, 2007. She and her family were unable to see their father for the last time when their father, 60, died of an "acute illness" while hospitalized.
1月底，夏女士查出肺部已感染。
At the end of January, Ms. Xia detected a lung infection.
2月4日，她在武汉市中心医院等来一个床位，随后入院治疗。
On 4 February, she was admitted to hospital after waiting for a bed at Wuhan Central Hospital.
2月11日，夏女士称她母亲身体康复了，11日上午已经出院。
On 11 February, Ms. Xia reported that her mother had recovered and had been discharged from the hospital on the morning of 11 February.
母亲出院后才得知父亲已经去世，伤心地哭了又哭。
After her mother left the hospital, she learned that her father had passed away and wept bitterly.
澎湃新闻将持续以日记的形式，记录夏女士一家在治疗期间所经历的种种。
The surging news will continue to take the form of a diary of what Ms. Xia's family went through during the treatment.
以下是夏女士的日记：2月11日 星期二 阴今天是我入院治疗的第八天，我每天的感觉就是饿，还没到饭点就开始饿了。
Today is my eighth day of hospital treatment. I feel hungry every day. I start to starve before the meal time.
好在有朋友给我送粥送汤来，医院的盒饭之外，我还能补充些营养。
Fortunately, I have friends to send soup porridge, hospital lunch box, I can add some nutrition.
其实家人也送了些饼干点心之类，但是我不想吃这些，我觉得要吃点天然健康的食物才有助于身体吸收，不给身体增加负担。
In fact, the family also sent some cookies and so on, but I do not want to eat these, I think to eat some natural and healthy food to help the body absorb, do not add to the burden.
今天早上，我抽了五管血用来复查，查出肝功能有点异常。
This morning, I took five tubes of blood for a reexamination and found that my liver function was a little abnormal.
哎，这该死的病毒，好像是要把我五脏六腑都攻击一遍，我可不会屈服！我昨天做的CT检查，今天出结果了，显示“复查有好转趋势”，我瞬间斗志昂扬，饭菜也多吃两口。
Hey, this damn virus, as if to attack my viscera all over again, I will not give in! I did yesterday's CT examination, today's results showed that "review has an improvement trend," I instantly high-spirited, the meals eat two more.
今天我妈身体康复已经出院了，虽然她还有点咳嗽，但是应该会慢慢好起来的。
Today, my mother is out of the hospital. Although she still has a cough, she should get better slowly.
之前，家人都瞒着我妈，没告诉她我爸去世的消息。
Before that, my family had been hiding from my mother and had not told her about my father's death.
她出院后就问我爸在哪里住院，要去找他。
After she left the hospital, she asked my father where he was hospitalized and wanted to find him.
现在瞒不住了，我跟她说了实情。
I can't hide it now. I told her the truth.
她伤心的哭了还哭，就在刚刚我给她打电话，她还在哭。
She cried and cried, just as I called her, she was still crying.
夏女士长期被消毒后的手。
Ms. Xia's hands after a long period of sterilization.
我知道她伤心难过，难以接受这个事实，但是我们只能向前看。
I know she is sad and sad to accept this fact, but we can only look ahead.
这段时间，我们一家七口都经历了太多难以承受的痛苦，我觉得我还算是坚强的。
During this time, my family of seven people have experienced too much unbearable pain, I think I am still strong.
我安慰我妈，“当下，家里人都在医院，我们都得把自己的身体照顾好。
I comforted my mother. "Right now, the family are in the hospital, and we all have to take care of ourselves.
”2020年2月11日本期编辑邢潭推荐阅读。
Xingtan, editor of the current issue of February 11, 2020.
